{
  "source_file": "Project Bus - Financial Due Diligence Scope of Work  1 1.docx",
  "format": "docx",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "Financial Due Diligence Work Plan",
      "style": "SLIPSHEET - Title",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 48.0
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "text": "Project Bus",
      "style": "SLIPSHEET - Subtitle",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 16.0
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "text": "January 15, 2025",
      "style": "Heading 2",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "text": "Fees",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "text": "Our professional fees will be based on the actual time required to complete the agreed upon work at discounted hourly rates identified for the professionals assigned to the engagement. Neither the amount of our fees nor the payment of our fees and expenses will be contingent upon transaction completion.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "text": "Financial Due Diligence – Excel workbook: $35,000 – $60,000",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "text": "Financial Due Diligence – Written report: Additional $20,000 - $25,000",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "text": "Out-of-scope requests: Based on actual time incurred at discounted hourly rates.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "text": "Above professional fees are subject to an administrative charge of 7% and sales taxes.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "text": "Financial Due Diligence",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "text": "Our work will include diligence on Great Canadian Coaches Inc., Great Canadian Fleet Services Inc., Great Canadian Holidays Inc., Big Blue Coach Inc., and 966021 Ontario Ltd. (collectively, “Target”), and in the historical periods, will concentrate on the last three fiscal years ended November 30, 20231, 2022 (“FY22”), 2023 (“FY23”) and 2024 (“FY24”) and the latest available year-to-date information.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "text": "Overview",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "text": "Meet with Target’s officers and management in order to develop an understanding of operations, including its:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "text": "Basis of financial information;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "text": "Organization structure;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "text": "Historical growth by geography; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "text": "Finance function, financial reporting framework and internal control environment.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "text": "Consistency of accounting policies",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "text": "Consider if the following accounting policies have been applied consistently within and across historical periods:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "text": "Revenue recognition;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "text": "Significant accounting estimates (e.g. inventory costing, allowance for doubtful accounts, etc.);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "text": "Capitalization policies;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "text": "Depreciation policies; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "text": "Recent or contemplated changes in accounting principles, procedures or estimates and provisions.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "text": "Quality / sustainability of earnings",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "text": "Identify, and where possible quantify, potential earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (“EBITDA”) normalization items by considering:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "text": "The impact of the normalization adjustments identified by Management;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "text": "Large, unusual or non-recurring events, or transactions that may have distorted results;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "text": "The impact of any changes to senior management or management team structure;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "text": "The impact of provisions (allowance for doubtful accounts, inventory obsolescence, other), management estimates or adjusting entries on the reported results;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "text": "The impact of foreign currency transactions;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "text": "The impact of related party transactions and shared services provided by other entities, if applicable;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "text": "The impact of any changes in accounting policies, procedures and estimates; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "text": "Other potential items identified during the due diligence process.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "text": "Supporting analyses to quality / sustainability of earnings",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "text": "Revenue and profitability trends",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of Target’s revenue and margins and inquire about:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "text": "Revenue and profitability by significant customer;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "text": "Revenue and profitability by customer type;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "text": "Revenue and profitability by customer profile (e.g., related party vs. third party);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "text": "Revenue and profitability by trip type (e.g., tours, day trips, etc.);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "text": "Impact of seasonality, if any;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "text": "Any non-recurring components of revenue; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "text": "Cut off procedures.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "text": "For each of the above items a) – d), inquire about key performance indicators such as volume (e.g., number of trips, etc.).",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "text": "Cost of revenues and Operating expenses",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of expenses and inquire about:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "text": "Direct costs (labour and benefits, etc.);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "text": "Employee compensation and related costs by function;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "text": "Selling, general, and administrative expenses;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "text": "Rent and utilities expense;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "text": "Historical operating expense trend as a % of revenue; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "text": "Unusual and extraordinary items.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "text": "Working capital",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "text": "Comment on working capital trends for the past 24 months;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "text": "Adjust working capital for any significant items which are considered to be non-recurring in nature;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "text": "Comment on the seasonality of working capital;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "text": "Comment on cash management procedures; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "text": "Understand trade ratio trends.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "text": "Supporting analyses to working capital",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "text": "Accounts receivable",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of accounts receivable and inquire and comment on:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "text": "Trade and non-trade balances;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "text": "Aging analysis and turnover analysis; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "text": "Allowance for uncollectible accounts, write-offs and reserves.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "text": "Inventory",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of inventory accounts and inquire and comment on:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "text": "Costing methodology;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "text": "Composition (e.g. raw materials, supplies, finished goods etc.); and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "text": "Turnover, aging and provisions.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "text": "Other assets and liabilities",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "text": "Prepare a summary of other assets and liabilities (including prepaid expenses and deposits, deferred revenue and customer deposits) and comment on unusual items, significant fluctuations and significant balances.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "text": "Accounts payable and accrued liabilities",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of accounts payable, accrued liabilities and customer deposits and inquire about:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "text": "Accounts payable aging and days outstanding;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "text": "Accrued liabilities;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "text": "Supplier settlement terms; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "text": "Other current and non-current liabilities.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "text": "Capital expenditure and fixed assets",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of historic and future capital cost requirements including:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "text": "Maintenance versus growth capital expenditures;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "text": "Other historical, deferred, and planned capital expenditures;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "text": "Historical replacement cycle and costs;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "text": "Utilization per unit; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "text": "Impairment write-downs and other issues.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "text": "Net Debt",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "text": "Prepare a summary of debt and debt-like items (e.g. notes payable, letters of credit, capital vendor payables, etc.), other assets, and liabilities and comment on unusual items, significant fluctuations and significant balances.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "text": "Related Party Transactions",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "text": "Inquire about and summarize related party transactions including:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "text": "Nature and extent of related party transactions; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "text": "Basis of pricing for arrangements with related parties.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "text": "Commitments and Contingencies",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "text": "Inquire about significant commitments and contingent liabilities including:",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "text": "Off-balance sheet liabilities;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "text": "Purchase commitments;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "text": "Operating and capital leases;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "text": "Incentive compensation and employee benefit obligations;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "text": "Expected or contingent liabilities (e.g. environmental, litigation, regulatory and tax); and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "text": "Pending or threatened litigation or investigations.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    }
  ],
  "tables": [],
  "headers_footers": []
}